  "prompt": "How can someone subscribe to Facebook topics on Quora?",
  "response": "To subscribe to Facebook topics on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log in to Quora:** Go to the [Quora website](https://www.quora.com) and log in to your account.\n   \n2. **Search for the Topic:** In the search bar at the top, type \"Facebook\" or the specific topic related to Facebook that you\u2019re interested in.\n   \n3. **Select the Topic:** From the search results, click on the relevant topic. This will take you to the page dedicated to that topic.\n\n4. **Follow the Topic:** On the topic page, look for a \"Follow Topic\" button or a \"+\" icon. Clicking this will subscribe you to the topic, and you'll start receiving updates and notifications related to it.\n\nAfter following the topic, you'll see answers, questions, and discussions related to Facebook in your feed, and you'll receive notifications about new content related to the topics you're interested in.\n\nFor mobile users, the steps are quite similar:\n\n1. **Open the Quora App:** Open the Quora app on your smartphone and log in.\n   \n2. **Use the Search Function:** Tap on the search icon and enter \"Facebook\".\n   \n3. **Navigate to the Topic:** Select the topic from the search results.\n   \n4. **Follow the Topic:** Tap \"Follow\" on the topic page.\n\nThis will ensure you stay updated with the latest questions, answers, and discussions about Facebook on Quora.",
